CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 6, 1957, pg. A8, reads: "O-O-O-Whee is Right! - The Co-eds, a new rhythm and blues singing group, sound off at their debut at the lawn party sponsored by the 300 Club, June 30. Striking a different fashion note with matching Bermuda shorts and jackets are, left to right: Nikki Nickens, James Henry, Boots Bray, Bob Worthington and Butch Thomas. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of rhythms and blues group, The Co-eds, wearing light colored bermuda shorts, dark socks, and dark jackets, from left: Nikki Nickens, James Henry, LouJeanne "Bootsie" Bray, Robert "Bob" Worthington, and Butch Thomas, posed outdoors
